Code reviews in BE
1. use DRY(don't repeat yourself) principle
2. use vairable/ configs instead of hard coding something that can be changed in future
3. make common functions
4. use map instead of pluck and use things which do less query
5. compute things previously(using include) instead of computing in loop
6. use update -> when callbacks required, update_column(s) -> no callbacks(always update updated_at)
7. api call name: no need of update if patch, create if post, get if get call.
8. Clear seperation of responsibility (route-> controller-> policy -> helper -> models)
9. Do validation of everything, never trust client input(can be from FE or from postman)
10. Do proper logging
11. Avoid N+1 queries, add indexing
12. Use trasactions on heavy DB queries.
13. Make migraitons idempotent
14. Avoid business logic in controller
15. Add documentation always
16. Check for performance
17. Add comments where things can't be directly understandable
18. Self review 